    "As the field pushes toward ever-larger models, our findings offer both a cautionary note and a path forward: larger models are not necessarily better when they disrupt the choreography of distributed information flow, and progress may hinge less on sheer scale and more on how transformers coordinate, scramble, and ultimately collapse information into a decision.",
